reviews.text:
I rented a car from Green Motion in Rabat in December. When I picked up the car, the employee who signed the documents ‚Äúhelped‚Äù me exit the parking lot but gave me wrong directions, which led to a small scratch on the car. When I returned the vehicle, a U‚ÄëSave employee did the check‚Äëin and then discussed the situation with the Green Motion agent, IMAN. She examined the existing scratch and I then noticed that a new scratch on the back appeared and was being taken into account in order to activate the insurance (I understood later that they needed two scratches to do so). I was charged 1‚ÄØ600‚ÄØ‚Ç¨ and asked to pay immediately, without my deposit being returned at that time. As a student, I did not have this amount available and spent an entire day trying to find an additional 1‚ÄØ600‚ÄØ‚Ç¨. This was a horrible experience and I strongly advise future customers to be extremely careful and to document the vehicle‚Äôs condition in detail at pick‚Äëup and BEFORE the drop‚Äëoff.

I have even been told by another rental agency that some agents may add new scratches at drop‚Äëoff to activate insurance and obtain a large payment. I am currently exploring legal options regarding this situation.

A little over two years ago, while working in Morocco, I was looking for a reliable car rental company with reasonable prices.

On the advice of a friend, the head of a major Moroccan government agency, I contacted Mr. Driss, the founder of Square Car, for my first rental.

In short, whether you're a tourist or traveling for business, based on my experience, I highly recommend Square Car.

A very negative, frustrating, and completely unprofessional experience.
I arrived on the day of my appointment. They informed me for the first time that for a simple diagnostic, the car would have to be kept for 48 hours, something that had never been explained beforehand.

The explanation they gave was that "this is how it works at Mercedes, and it's the same in Europe and Germany," which is completely false and misleading.

In Europe, when there is a 48-hour wait, they give advance notice or clearly explain that there is a staff shortage or a queue; they don't hide behind excuses like "this is how it is at Mercedes and in Germany."

There is no Mercedes-Benz policy that requires a car to be held for 48 hours for a diagnostic. What really exists is a lack of staff, overcrowding, and poor organization, but they prefer to hide it behind generic excuses.

And after 7 days of waiting for a call from the workshop, no one contacted me. On the day of my appointment, after all that waiting, they told me this.

The service from the workshop office (the woman) was completely unprofessional. Zero respect for the customer's time. They changed their story as it suited them and didn't give clear answers from the beginning.

Very disappointing.

Even more surprising is that when I went to the service center in person, I was refused service on the grounds that a prior phone appointment was required, even though the phone itself went unanswered.

This approach puts customers in a vicious cycle and reflects unprofessional service quality. It also raises serious questions about the respect shown for customers' time and needs.

I urge your management to take the necessary measures urgently to improve communication with customers and ensure effective booking channels, because the continuation of this situation may lead many customers, including myself, to seek other service providers.

reviews.name: Yassir El Aboudi
reviews.text:
Disappointing Experience and Breach of Trust at ≈†koda Rabat
I am writing this review to share a deeply frustrating and ultimately negative experience I had with ≈†koda Rabat.
On June 12th, I placed an order for a new car and was given a promised delivery timeline of three months. I paid the full amount in cash upfront, expecting a smooth transaction.
The initial disappointment came after the promised three-month window. When the car was finally presented to me, it was not the vehicle I had ordered. The specifications were incorrect, representing a clear failure on their part to fulfill the contract.
Given that I had paid in full, the subsequent process of trying to recover my money became an unexpected and incredibly difficult struggle. It took far too much effort and stress to simply get my own cash back.
To make matters worse, despite the significant inconvenience, the delivery failure, and the protracted refund process, there was no commercial gesture (aucun geste commercial) offered by the sales managers or leadership to acknowledge the breach of promise and the terrible customer experience.
I used to be a fan of the ≈†koda brand, but the way I was treated by this dealership has turned that admiration into intense dislike. They showed a complete lack of professionalism, accountability, and customer care.
My Advice to Future Customers:
Be extremely cautious and protect yourself. When you sign the purchase order (bon de commande), make absolutely sure that every single specification and feature you are ordering is explicitly and accurately written down. This written proof is your only protection against a situation like mine, and will give you the necessary leverage should you need to take legal action (sue them) if they fail to deliver on their promise.
I strongly advise others to think twice before doing business with this specific dealership.

24/12/2025
UPDATE: Zero Follow-Up and Better Alternatives
Despite the dealership‚Äôs "public" reply asking for my contact details (which I sent immediately on September 29th), I have received absolutely no response. It is clear that their reply was a generic PR tactic to look helpful to the public while continuing to ignore the customer in private. There has been no follow-up, no apology, and no accountability.
I have since taken my business elsewhere and purchased a Jetour T2. Not only was it more affordable and better equipped, but the customer service was worlds apart from the unprofessionalism I experienced at ≈†koda Rabat.
If you value your time, your money, and basic respect as a consumer, I suggest looking at other brands. ≈†koda Rabat has proven they are not interested in keeping their promises or resolving their mistakes.

reviews.name: Customer Guide
reviews.text:
Scam alert ‚Äì avoid this car rental at Casablanca Airport

This car rental company uses a dishonest tactic to take your money. Upon arrival at Casablanca Airport, they falsely mark your confirmed reservation as a ‚Äúno-show‚Äù, which automatically voids the booking and causes you to lose your prepaid amount.

Then, while you‚Äôre already there with no car, they suddenly ‚Äúoffer‚Äù another vehicle outside the original reservation for three times the original price.

So they profit twice:
1.	They keep your money by canceling your reservation as a no-show.
2.	They rent you the same car (or similar) on the spot at triple the price.

This is not an accident or bad service  it‚Äôs a deliberate scam tactic targeting travelers arriving tired and with limited options. I strongly advise avoiding this company and booking with a reputable international rental brand instead.
